name: Ratna Sagar Family Restaurant & Bar (Calangute)

reviews.review_text:
Ratna Sagar (Navarthna Udupi Pure Veg)
Visit month First week July 2024

This restaurant offers a unique dual-cuisine experience - vegetarian food upstairs and non-vegetarian downstairs towards the beach. The location is perfect for enjoying a beach view while dining.
We visited the upatairs floor and tried vegetarian food of navarthna veg and were impressed. We ordered veg handi, daal, jeera rice, and paneer jalfrezi, and all the dishes were delicious. The restrooms were also clean and well-maintained.

As we were staying near to the beach and only this restaurent was good  The service was good and one can enjoy sea while eating

We have tried noodles, crab ,panner and  green chicken and icecream taste was good and two water bottle cost 180rs ! Price was too high .. I like that staff was nicely responding and night I saw that dj was playing nicely visit once night experience was good.

Good place to chillout

As we were staying near to the beach and only this restaurent was good at moderate price hence we went there twice on 23rd August 2023. The service was good and one can enjoy sea while eating. This place does not have AC but big coolers and sea breeze also could be enjoyed. For lunch we ordered 2 kulcha, 2 naan, 1 chicken vindaloo and 1 egg fried rice. The total bill was 935/-. Kulchas did not have stuffings because we know that generally kulchas have stuffings. Moreover the size of the kulchas were small comparing to other restaurents. For dinner, we took 1 chicken 65, 1 chicken lollypop, 1 mix noodles and 2 bottles of turbourg large. Mix noodle was not upto the mark especially according to price. Others's taste were more than average. Live music was playing so one who cannot bear high sound could feel bothered but we enjoyed it.
The major dissapointment was 2 bottles of drink were charged 180 per bottle where printed price was 110. Then they also took 22% VAT. I have never seen any goaneese restaurent is taking VAT on liquor. The total bill amount was 1355.
Positive side of the restaurent were their view of the sea and their staff Jhuma who was taking utmost care of the guests.

description:
**Ratna Sagar Family Restaurant & Bar: Dining by the Sea**

Nestled in the vibrant locale of Calangute, Ratna Sagar Family Restaurant & Bar has earned a commendable rating of 4.2 out of 5, driven by insights from 2,000 enthusiastic reviewers. Renowned for its coastal allure, the restaurant is a notable spot for beach lovers, featuring tags like "beach" (81 mentions), "karaoke" (73 mentions), and a focus on "food and service" (30 mentions). This dual-cuisine venue caters to a diverse clientele with delightful vegetarian options upstairs and a tantalizing non-vegetarian selection downstairs, ensuring it has something for everyone.

**Ambiance & Design**

With a casual yet inviting atmosphere, Ratna Sagar boasts simple decor that complements its beachside location. The seating arrangement allows guests to relish panoramic views of the sea, enhancing the overall dining experience. The ambiance is further enlivened by local live music and a DJ, creating a perfect backdrop for a night out. The natural sea breeze flows through, with large coolers in place for those who prefer a cooler setting, although the establishment does not feature air-conditioning. Reviewers have praised the cleanliness of facilities, highlighting an emphasis on hospitality even in the restroom areas.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The restaurant's menu showcases a rich array of both vegetarian and non-vegetarian delights. Diners have recommended the Navarthna Veg specialties, including the hearty veg handi, savory daal, and aromatic jeera rice, which are all catered upstairs. Meanwhile, the downstairs menu offers engaging options like chicken vindaloo, noodles, and crab, celebrating local cuisines with a twist. The presentation of dishes is appealing, with color and freshness at the forefront, although some patrons noted certain items, like the kulchas, could benefit from more generous stuffing. Pricing is perceived as moderate, yet some guests have flagged that certain beverages are marked higher than expected. 

**Customer Experience & Service**

Service at Ratna Sagar is lauded for its warmth and responsiveness, with several reviews mentioning attentive staff who go the extra mile to enhance the customer experience. Guests have particularly highlighted the efforts of a staff member named Jhuma, commending her focus on guest satisfaction. The restaurant welcomes walk-ins but living up to a busy atmosphere, reservations might be wise, especially during peak hours. 

**Popularity & Reviews**

The restaurant's popularity can be felt across social media platforms, where patrons rave about the unique setting, quality food, and vibrant atmosphere. Despite a few critiques regarding pricing and food consistency, the majority of diners leave with fond memories and a desire to return. A night with karaoke and live music creates an electrifying vibe, bringing together a mix of locals and tourists.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The customer-provided photos further capture the essence of dining at Ratna Sagar, showcasing the splendid beach views, lively décor, and beautifully plated meals. Images reveal the inviting setup of the restaurant and hint at the buzz during peak hours, making it apparent why this spot is favored for both casual and celebratory gatherings.

In conclusion, Ratna Sagar Family Restaurant & Bar is not only a delightful culinary destination but also an experience enriched with the sea's rhythm and vibrant local culture. Whether you’re after a quick bite or a full dining experience, this restaurant has carved a niche that is worth exploring.
